<div style="display: none;">
    <div id="abs-1"><p>This paper investigates the information needs of librarians at Niger Delta University, analyzing current resource availability, digital literacy gaps, and infrastructural challenges to propose actionable improvements for academic libraries in the region.</p></div>
    <div id="abs-2"><p>This historical study explores the pivotal role of the Ibibio Union in driving educational development across Ibibioland between 1928 and 1966. It highlights the Union's strategies in mobilizing community resources for educational infrastructure.</p></div>
    <div id="abs-3"><p>An exploration of the intricate relationship between power dynamics and poetics in the Niger Delta. The research analyzes literary expressions and artistic resistance as tools for navigating socio-political struggles within the oil-rich region.</p></div>
    <div id="abs-4"><p>This paper details the contributions of the National Inland Waterways Authority (NIWA) to the economic and structural development of Nigeria's inland waterways from 1997 to 2014, assessing both policy successes and operational limitations.</p></div>
    <div id="abs-5"><p>This research examines the detrimental effects of ethnic conflicts on the civic education and socio-political engagement of youths in the Niger Delta, arguing for curriculum reforms that emphasize peace-building and unity.</p></div>
